The Good Party has called for action against DA Chief Whip in the National Assembly Natasha Mazzone over her qualifications. It says Mazzone’s biographies on various websites have been altered from having legal qualifications to having none. The Good Party’s Brett Herron says Mazzone’s updated Wikipedia biography listed two universities as her Alma Maters, but her highest academic qualification is matric. He says another website says she did not complete a law degree. The Good Party says it has also laid criminal charges against DA Western Cape leader and Transport MEC Bonginkosi Madikizela. He’s been suspended following revelations that he misled the public about his academic qualifications. Alan Winde on suspending MEC Bonginkosi Madikizela: 